        <para>* Engine must be at normal operating temperature.</para>
        <para>&#8224; Refer to "Performance Data Guidelines," in this section.</para>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>COMPLAINTS OF STALLING OR ROUGH RUNNING MAY BE THE RESULT OF INCORRECT LOW IDLE SPEED.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <para>Check and adjust low idle speed as follows:</para>
        <specpara>
            <important>
                <para>ON VEHICLES EQUIPPED WITH AUTOMATIC TRANSMISSIONS, LOW IDLE SPEED IS RECRODED WITH THE
                    TRANSMISSION IN GEAR, EMERGENCY BRAKE ENGAGED AND FOOT BRAKE HELD. MANUAL TRANSMISSIONS MUST BE IN
                    NEUTRAL WITH THE EMERGENCY BRAKE ENGAGED.
                </para>
            </important>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Attach tachometer.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Start engine and warm to normal operating temperature.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate low idle adjustment screw on fuel injection pump (Figure
                <hotlnk xrefid="ef4600512">5.12</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="ef4600512" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg10175" filename="../figcg1/CG10175.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 5.12 Low Idle Adjustment</caption>
            </figure>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">* - Manual specified with latest revision</emph>
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Release the throttle linkage completely and allow the engine to idle. Refer to the
                "Performance Data Guidelines" or the engine emission label mounted on the valve cover, for the correct
                low idle specification.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If low idle speed is not within specifications, turn adjusting screw (Figure
                <hotlnk xrefid="ef4600512">5.12</hotlnk>) to obtain correct idle speed. Low idle adjustment screw must
                contact stop on injection pump.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Adjust cold idle solenoid (Figures
                <hotlnk xrefid="ef4600513">5.13</hotlnk>
                and
                <hotlnk xrefid="ef4600514">5.14</hotlnk>) to 825 &#177; 25 RPM with the engine at normal operating
                temperature as follows:
            </para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the HPCA Solenoid. Refer to Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4600513">5.13</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Energize the cold idle solenoid using a jumper wire [made locally] connected between the
                    ESO and cold idle solenoid terminals. Refer to Figure
                    <hotlnk document="e460_29.xml" xrefid="ef4600507">5.7</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Move the throttle lever (2, Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4600514">5.14</hotlnk>) off idle position (1, Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4600514">5.14</hotlnk>) to allow the cold idle solenoid plunger to extend.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Turn the cold idle solenoid plunger in or out using an open end wrench until 825 &#177;
                    25 RPM is achieved when the plunger pushes against the throttle lever. Refer to Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4600514">5.14</hotlnk>.
                </para>
                <figure id="ef4600513" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg11955" filename="../figcg1/CG11955.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 5.13 Activating Cold Advance using Jumper Wire</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4600514" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg11983" filename="../figcg1/CG11983.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 5.14 Cold Idle Solenoid Adjustment</caption>
                </figure>
            </step2>
        </step1>
